    Scope and Contents
The Undergraduate Council Records (1984-) consist of the Council's agendas, minutes, working papers and memos.  The Undergraduate Council, formed in 1984 as a standing subcommittee of the Curriculum and Academic Standards Committee, recommends policies and procedures for program development and change, including course and catalogue approval, program review and deletion, the development and evaluation of admissions and degree requirements including academic load, probation guidelines and admission and closure policies.  The Council also advises the Faculty Senate on all undergraduate matters including financial aid and honor policies.  
  
